Package database

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Database
    Database is the class that holds responsibility for every table that exists in a database.
    DatabaseMenu
    Creates the main menu of the database.
    Entry
    An Entry object is supposed to be a record (row) in the database.
    Field
    A Field object is a data structure for a single piece of data.
    Main  
    Menu
    Superclass whose members are going to be inherited both by TableMenu and DatabaseMenu classes.
    Search
    Searches the database to find something.
    Standards
    Standards ensure that no single table/field/element in the database have an unacceptable value such as a single whitespace.
    Table
    A Table object represent a data structure with rows and columns that exists in a database.
    TableMenu
    Prints the menu.
    TransferData
    Exports data of Database's tables to Excel Sheets, which can be imported at another time.
